## LECTURE 1.2 — SCOPE DEFINITION: WHAT GOES IN, WHAT STAYS OUT

49
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:20,000
One of the most common mistakes in SOC 2 preparation
is defining your scope too broadly or too narrowly.

50
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Too broad and you will drown in evidence collection.
Too narrow and customers will question whether the report
covers what matters to them.

51
00:00:40,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Let me show you how to define the perfect system boundary.
The key principle is this.
Include everything required to deliver your service.

52
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Exclude everything that customers do not depend on.
I am going to create a complete system boundary document
for our financial RAG agent.

53
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:50,000
Run cat greater than soc2 forward slash system-boundary dot yaml.
This time we are adding system components and data flows.

54
00:01:50,000 --> 00:02:20,000
