## LECTURE 1.3 — CONTROL SELECTION: WHICH CONTROLS APPLY TO YOU

81
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Now that we understand the five Trust Service Criteria
and have defined our system boundary,
it is time to select specific controls.

82
00:00:30,000 --> 00:01:00,000
SOC 2 does not tell you exactly which controls to implement.
You have to choose based on your system's risks.
The SOC 2 Trust Services Criteria are organized into nine categories.

83
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Often called CC1 through CC9.
But for most SaaS companies, you will focus on CC6 through CC9.
Let me walk you through which ones matter for our RAG system.

