## LECTURE 1.4 — EVIDENCE COLLECTION STRATEGY: AUTOMATE EVERYTHING

113
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Evidence is the currency of SOC 2.
Without evidence, controls do not exist.
The worst thing that can happen during an audit is the auditor asks
for evidence of a control and you cannot produce it.

114
00:00:30,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Manual evidence collection is error-prone and miserable.
You will forget to collect it, collect the wrong thing,
or collect it at the wrong time.
The solution is automation.

115
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Let me show you how to build an automated evidence collection pipeline.
Create dot github forward slash workflows forward slash evidence-collection dot yaml.

116
00:01:30,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Name colon SOC 2 Evidence Collection.
On colon schedule colon dash cron colon zero zero asterisk asterisk asterisk.
That is daily at midnight.
And workflow_dispatch for manual trigger.

117
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:30,000
The collect-evidence job runs on ubuntu-latest.
Steps include checkout, then for each control we collect evidence.

118
00:02:30,000 --> 00:03:00,000
For CC6.1, collect API key configuration.
Run kubectl get secret api-keys in the financial-rag namespace.
Output to evidence forward slash CC6.1 forward slash api-keys with date.

119
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:30,000
For CC6.6, collect RDS encryption status.
Run aws rds describe-db-instances for financial-rag-prod.
Query StorageEncrypted. Output to evidence forward slash CC6.6 forward slash rds-encryption with date.

120
00:03:30,000 --> 00:04:00,000
For CC6.7, collect TLS certificate expiration.
Run kubectl get secret api-tls, pipe to jq and base64 decode,
then openssl x509 to get end date.
Output to evidence forward slash CC6.7 forward slash cert-expiry with date.

121
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:30,000
For CC7.1, collect uptime metrics.
Run curl to Prometheus querying up job financial-rag-api.
Output to evidence forward slash CC7.1 forward slash uptime with date.

122
00:04:30,000 --> 00:05:00,000
For CC7.2, collect alert configurations.
Run kubectl get prometheusrules across all namespaces.
Output to evidence forward slash CC7.2 forward slash alert-rules with date.

123
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:30,000
For CC7.4, collect backup status.
Run velero backup get in JSON format.
Output to evidence forward slash CC7.4 forward slash backup-status with date.

124
00:05:30,000 --> 00:06:00,000
For CC8.1, collect recent deployments.
Run kubectl rollout history for the API deployment.
Output to evidence forward slash CC8.1 forward slash deployments with date.

125
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Finally, upload to S3 evidence bucket.
Run aws s3 sync evidence to s3://financial-rag-soc2-evidence with date folder.

126
00:06:30,000 --> 00:07:00,000
Now let me show you the evidence retention policy.
You need to keep evidence for the audit period plus typically seven years
for SOC 2 Type II.

127
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:30,000
In terraform forward slash s3-evidence-lifecycle dot tf.
Create an aws_s3_bucket_lifecycle_configuration for the evidence bucket.

128
00:07:30,000 --> 00:08:00,000
First rule. id colon archive-after-1-year.
Transition to GLACIER after 365 days.
Second rule. id colon delete-after-7-years.

129
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:30,000
Expiration after 2555 days.
Which is seven years.

130
00:08:30,000 --> 00:09:00,000
Here is the complete evidence inventory you should maintain.
CC6.1 evidence type API key logs from CloudWatch with retention one year.
CC6.6 evidence type RDS encryption status from AWS Config with retention seven years.

131
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:30,000
CC6.7 evidence type TLS cert expiry from kubectl with retention seven years.
CC7.1 evidence type uptime metrics from Prometheus with retention one year.

132
00:09:30,000 --> 00:10:00,000
CC7.2 evidence type alert configurations from Git with retention seven years.
CC7.4 evidence type backup logs from Velero with retention seven years.

133
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:30,000
CC8.1 evidence type PR approvals from GitHub API with retention seven years.
CC9.2 evidence type vendor assessments from S3 with retention seven years.

134
00:10:30,000 --> 00:11:00,000
Now create a template for documenting each piece of evidence.
Make a file called evidence forward slash README dot md.

135
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:30,000
Start with evidence format standard.
All evidence must include timestamp of collection,
control ID, description of what the evidence proves,
collection method, and retention period.

136
00:11:30,000 --> 00:12:00,000
For CC6.1, the file is CC6.1 forward slash api-keys dash YYYYMMDD dot yaml.
It proves API keys are properly configured and rotated.
Collection is automated daily. Retention one year.

137
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:30,000
For CC6.6, the file is CC6.6 forward slash rds-encryption dash YYYYMMDD dot json.
It proves RDS instance has encryption enabled.
Automated daily. Retention seven years.

138
00:12:30,000 --> 00:13:00,000
For CC7.1, the file is CC7.1 forward slash uptime dash YYYYMMDD dot json.
It proves system meets ninety-nine point nine percent availability SLO.
Automated daily. Retention one year.

139
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:30,000
Now create a validation script.
In scripts forward slash validate-evidence dot sh.
The script takes a date parameter defaulting to today.

140
00:13:30,000 --> 00:14:00,000
It sets evidence directory to evidence forward slash that date.
Then for each control including CC6.1, CC6.6, CC6.7, CC7.1, CC7.2, CC7.4, and CC8.1.
It checks if the control directory has any files.

141
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:30,000
If missing, it outputs a red X and exits with error.
If all present, it outputs green check marks
and says all evidence present.

142
00:14:30,000 --> 00:15:00,000
Your lab exercise is to run the evidence collection pipeline
and verify the artifacts.
Set up the GitHub Actions workflow I showed.

143
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:30,000
Or create a local script if you are not using GitHub Actions.
Run it once manually, then check that evidence files are created
in your S3 bucket or local directory.

144
00:15:30,000 --> 00:16:00,000
Verify that each control has at least one evidence file.
If anything is missing, note what is missing.
That is your gap analysis for remediation.

145
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:30,000
Once you have completed that, move on to Lecture one point five.
