## LECTURE 1.7 — REMEDIATION PLANNING: CLOSING EVERY GAP BEFORE FIELDWORK

203
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Your readiness check will almost certainly reveal gaps.
That is normal. Every company has them.
The key is having a plan to close them before your audit.

204
00:00:30,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Let me show you the most common gaps I see
and exactly how to fix them.

205
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Create soc2 forward slash remediation-tracker dot yaml.
Under remediations, list each gap.

206
00:01:30,000 --> 00:02:00,000
First gap. gap colon No API key rotation policy.
control colon CC6.1.
owner colon at sign security dash team.
due_date colon 2026-04-15.
status colon in_progress.

207
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:30,000
steps colon dash Create rotation Lambda function.
dash Update documentation.
dash Test rotation in staging.
evidence colon A pull request URL.

208
00:02:30,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Second gap. gap colon RDS not encrypted in staging.
control colon CC6.6.
owner colon at sign platform dash team.
due_date colon 2026-05-01.
status colon planned.

209
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:30,000
steps colon dash Take snapshot of unencrypted database.
dash Restore as encrypted.
dash Update Terraform config.
dash Verify application connectivity.

210
00:03:30,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Third gap. gap colon Missing vendor assessment for OpenAI.
control colon CC9.2.
owner colon at sign compliance dash team.
due_date colon 2026-04-30.
status colon not_started.

211
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:30,000
steps colon dash Request SOC 2 report from OpenAI.
dash Review controls.
dash Document in vendor register.

212
00:04:30,000 --> 00:05:00,000
Fourth gap. gap colon No quarterly restore test performed.
control colon CC7.4.
owner colon at sign platform dash team.
due_date colon 2026-04-15.
status colon in_progress.

213
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:30,000
steps colon dash Write restore test script.
dash Schedule first test.
dash Document results.
evidence colon A link to the tests directory.

214
00:05:30,000 --> 00:06:00,000
Here is a remediation timeline in Gantt chart format.
For access control, API key rotation starts 2026-03-15 for fourteen days.
RBAC documentation starts after that for seven days.

215
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:30,000
For encryption, RDS encryption in staging starts 2026-03-20 for twenty-one days.
TLS certificate automation starts 2026-04-01 for fourteen days.

216
00:06:30,000 --> 00:07:00,000
For operations, restore test script starts 2026-03-25 for ten days.
On-call schedule starts 2026-03-20 for five days.

217
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:30,000
For vendors, OpenAI assessment starts 2026-04-01 for fourteen days.
AWS review starts 2026-04-01 for seven days.

218
00:07:30,000 --> 00:08:00,000
For each gap, you need a clear description of what is missing.
The specific control it affects.
An owner assigned. A due date.

219
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:30,000
Concrete steps to fix it.
And evidence of completion.

220
00:08:30,000 --> 00:09:00,000
Here is how to prioritize remediation.
Critical priority means missing control with high risk.
For example, no API authentication.
Timeline less than two weeks.

221
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:30,000
High priority means partial control with medium risk.
For example, manual key rotation only.
Timeline less than four weeks.

222
00:09:30,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Medium priority means control exists but weak evidence.
For example, no audit logging.
Timeline less than eight weeks.

223
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:30,000
Low priority means control exists but needs documentation.
For example, policy not documented.
Timeline less than twelve weeks.

224
00:10:30,000 --> 00:11:00,000
Your lab exercise is to create a remediation plan
for the gaps you identified in your readiness check.
Use the tracker template I provided.

225
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:30,000
Assign owners and due dates.
Review with your team and get commitment on the timeline.
Once you have completed that, move on to Lecture one point eight.

226
00:11:30,000 --> 00:12:00,000
Where we will assemble the final evidence package.

